{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Coaching-move suggestion (from live use): plan-review has a pass-4 COACH that emits a productive next-move per finding. When a finding asserts a symbol/library-fact is absent AND the referenced name looks like it could be a third-party library symbol (CamelCase, zero rebar-repo hits, plausibly under an installed dependency's namespace), the coach should suggest the EVIDENCE-INJECTION move: 'Run a small offline experiment that proves the library behavior (import the symbol, show its MRO / a canned-response propagation) and paste the captured output into the ticket description (a `## Verified library behavior (experiment log)` section). The verifier pass then has concrete, in-context evidence to DROP the absence finding.' This makes the gate self-healing against the repo-scoped-read blind spot rather than dead-ending the author in an unremediable BLOCK. Empirically observed to work: embedding a captured pydantic_ai.exceptions experiment log (showing ContentFilterError/IncompleteToolCall resolve as UnexpectedModelBehavior subclasses) gave the verifier grounds to drop the false 'symbol does not exist' findings. Consider adding this as a named coaching template keyed on the absence-finding + third-party-symbol heuristic. Also fold the experiment-log convention into docs/plan-review-gate.md so authors know the move exists."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783629858719180001,"uuid":"03e48bc2-e937-4996-88c4-ab63e3df923d"}